{
  "texts": [
    "Retrieval tools.For each user, our attribute-oriented retrieval tools accept an attribute pattern 𝑎 𝑡 and a specified item set size $𝐾, subsequently returning the matching candidate item set.",
    "An intuitive way is creating dedicated models tailored to each attribute pattern.",
    "However, it is markedly inefficient to fully train and store separate models for every possible attribute permutation.",
    "To address this, we introduce a two-stage method for managing attributespecific variations:Pre-training.",
    "The pre-training stage is for the original model with no attribute-specific consideration."
  ]
}